    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offered is a museum-grade 1997 Porsche 911 (993) Carrera, the final evolution of the air-cooled era. This example features the M64/21 3.6L flat-six engine equipped with the Varioram resonance intake system for optimized mid-range torque. Power is delivered via a precise G50/20 six-speed manual transaxle with a factory-optioned limited-slip differential. The chassis remains exceptionally taut, utilizing the LSA multi-link rear axle and four-piston Monobloc calipers over cross-drilled, ventilated rotors. This vehicle is mechanically flawless, showing a completely dry undercarriage, zero parasitic draws, and perfect compression across all cylinders. The original finish is preserved with no road rash, and the interior retains its factory-fresh Nappa leather scent and structural integrity.",
